description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Community Nurses play an important role in supporting patients to remain at home. Your role as a community nurse will help the NHS meet the needs of elderly, disabled or vulnerable patients who may not be able to easily visit the GP surgery or hospital. As an essential part of the Multidisciplinary Team, you will be required to work alongside Doctors, Therapist’s, Heath Care support Workers and Social workers in delivering a gold standard approach to care to assist in optimising independence as well as also supporting families whose relatives are approaching end of life&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;As a Community Nurse you work independently as well as in a team. You will see a vast variety of patients, including: catheter care, advanced wound care, palliative/end of life care, IV therapy, Venepuncture etc… &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Southern Health takes pride in being caring, competent and compassionate, and we expect our staff to commit to and demonstrate these values. We offer excellent development opportunities and training that can be directed towards your needs/goals. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span&gt; No car…no problem!’ The Trust offers a lease car scheme, subject to eligibility, if you are interested in more information please contact Hollie Winkworth on 02380 475160&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;If you are unsure if the community is for you then we offer a shadowing morning. Please call Hollie Winkworth on 02380 475160 for details.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Watch our video to see why you should work for us!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;*********£2,500 ‘Golden Hello’ Payment**********&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Awarded with this vacancy!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Apply now and if you are successfully recruited you will receive £2,500&lt;strong&gt;- does not apply to current HIOW NHS Staff&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
